newsitem.title: USA: US West Coast products stay notionally flat late.
newsitem.headline: US West Coast products stay notionally flat late.

text.p: Operators shut Unocal's 125,000 barrel per day crude unit early on Thursday.
Jet fuel in Los Angeles was steady between 71 and 72 cents a gallon late on Friday.
CARB diesel held at 71/72.50 cents, after slipping a half cent earlier. Low-sulphur diesel, which meets federal rather than California pollution standards, was unchanged at 68.50/69.50 cents.
Conventional-grade gasoline in Los Angeles stayed at 65.25/66.25 cents.
CARB-grade gasoline remained at 69.00/70.00 cents late on Friday.
